message: "If you use Groundtruth in your research, please cite it as below."
title: "Groundtruth: an AI reliability platform"
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Sanjay
    email: sanmanivas@ucdavis.edu
    affiliation: "University of California, Davis"
version: 0.8.0
date-released: "2026-07-18"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/Sanjaayyy7/GroundTruth"
keywords:
  - ai-safety
  - evaluation
  - llm
  - red-team
  - agents
  - reliability
abstract: >-
  Groundtruth evaluates whether AI systems fail and explains why. One
  platform spine (trace, eval, dataset, validation engines) powers
  AgentProbe, an offline deterministic red-team evaluation for tool-using
  agents with an explanatory failure taxonomy. Detector quality is itself
  measured against a hand-labeled validation set, misses included, and the
  repository audits its own claims, evidence, and structure in CI.
